Selling Sunset's Chelsea Lazkani, Emma Hernan, and Mary Fitzgerald led their castmates in arriving at the 2022 People's Choice Awards on Tuesday evening.

The Netflix personalities all dressed to the nines in glittering gowns at the star-studded affair held at Santa Monica's Barker Hangar.

Each of their dresses had high slits as Chelsea sported a nude pink sheer variety, Emma wore a flesh color, and Mary opted for silver.

Mary was a sight to see as she displayed her perky cleavage with her look's plunging neckline that stretched to the center of her torso.

Along with wide side cut-outs that exposed her glowy skin, the fashionable frock had a sparkling waistband that hugged her midsection.

The outfit had reflective silvery beads that faded gradually as her dress extended to the floor with a modest train flowing behind her.

The TV star and real estate mogul styled her blonde locks in a side part and pulled it into a low and chic, wispy updo.

This is a story to help other consignment shops out and give some education. In our new generation as humans we are now trusting technology and apps to help us with better business practices. Human feeling is always the best. As a Reseller and Stylist I'm always looking for the best deals for my clients. On March 7th I went into one of my favorite boutiques called 2nd street and I saw a Chanel 19 belt bag Retail cost $4900 and it was reselling for $1200 !! a little dirty but I can get it cleaned by Chanel. When the SA opened up the case and when I touched and smelled it something didn't feel right the SA told me the bag was Authenticated by Entrupy and we trust the Entrupy report. Because everyone uses entrupy i trusted it but it from my feelings and touching it was too good to be true. I took it to my SA at Chanel and she told me we cannot service this item. HMMMM so did I get Scammed ? I knew the bag was fake ! I sent the bag twice to Real Authentication and confirmed twice the bag was fake even when I sent it with a certificate of authenticity. I called 2nd street to return the bag and they told me we cant give your money back but we can buy the bag back for $300 dollars and resell it. I went to a CHANEL expert who is amazing by the name ZEKO Authentication who specializes in Chanel bags and told me the bag was not  REAL. Called customer service one more time  and told them it was not real and I wanted my money back and i got the same responses `` sorry the bag was authenticated by Entrupy the accuracy is 99.1 %  The long story short to all you consignment shops stop trusting your business with a Machine cause all technology make mistakes. I hate when stores are say " Enturpy authenticated it " how about a you actually looking at the item and touching and smelling it ! This post is to educated boutiques on resell with clients and 2nd street i hope you see this to give me back my money I have spent over $30,000 in your boutique and i hope you give me a refund // UPDATE ETRUPY CANCELLED THE AUTHENTICATION

Quote from Vice magazine - So who exactly is masterminding the fashion development of Selling Sunset? Most of the show’s main cast now work with stylists to pick out their outfits for each scene, as well as glam squads to do their full hair and makeup. Sammie M is an LA-based stylist who works with Mary Fitzgerald and Amanza Smith from the show, as well as the other girls if they’re having a “fashion emergency”. 

Selling Sunset estate agents dressed in outlandish outfits

“They’re all like, in competition,” said Sammie, discussing how the girls are looking to build their personal brands on social media. “Basically, all the girls are out for themselves, and they're just trying to step it up because now, the way social media is, you have to step it up.” 

And even one of the girls he says is really into fashion has reached out asking to work with him if they get commissioned for future seasons, because she wants to “take it up a notch.” 

“It's becoming a show where everybody watches the clothes, pretty much,” Sammie explains. “Some people now, instead of watching for the houses, they’re watching for the fashion.”

He points out that reality shows with wealthy, independent women like Selling Sunset have plugged the gap left by Sex and the City, which ruled supreme as the most popular fashion TV show for decades.

I was discredited by @chrishell.stause for a shoot I had worked on which was produced by My agent Fahad Ali @bookmanagement .  The truth behind it was that the original model we had booked was @thechristinequinn , however Christine announced her pregnancy right after her trip to Bali in 2021, so my agent had to quickly find a replacement as everything was already in place. 

In a recent DM @chrishell.stause attacked me and discredited my work and bullied me. I’m not sure what medication she’s on but she clearly “forgot” that I had styled her. @chrishell.stause , you talk about being authentic and here’s my truth babe! Stay in your lane and give credit where credit is due. @thechristinequinn wish the shoot went as planned so I wouldn’t have to deal with such unprofessionalism and “amnesia”. My agent who produced this shoot even paid for Chrishell’s studio and glam team and was also NEVER credited .This was one of Chrishell’s best shoots in 2021 and was published numerous times including in @Forbes magazine  and @elle_magazine . 
@chrishell.stause - An apology would be appreciated !

7000 people in the arena today and STILL every time I go out on stage, I get the same sensation… this feeling of FUCK ME I’M ACTUALLY HERE 😳😍 then pure gratitude fills my soul, to the point I often cry and my makeup smudges 🫠🤭 

Knowing how far I’ve come from only a few years ago when I had died inside.. I never thought I’d escape the walls of my own mind or the battle against the sickness I was facing. Let alone get out of the financial debt I had accumulated….

But I knew somewhere in my heart we must all go through things so we can evolve and grow. And even at the time as hard as it felt, I knew there was something greater for me in the world… so I made an agreement with the universe/God, however, you want to call it and I said…. 

“If you heal me now and bring me out of this dark time, I promise to go forth and share it with the world!!” And that is exactly what I have done and I continue to do because I’m not just doing this for me anymore, I’m doing this for someONE else I can change the life of today ‼️

To help even 1 person transform their mindset, so they can transform their life, even when they feel like it’s unchangeable..

It’s always changeable!

YOU ARE UNSTOPPABLE and you cannot be defeated. If you’ve read this far this really is for you. 

They cannot stop you, nor can your circumstances.  Any day, anytime, you can decide to change your life, and it all starts in your heart and your mind…. It will be you up here soon telling YOUR irresistible story I hope 🤞🙏🏼

This was one of the BEST MOMENTS of my life! Receiving the VANGUARD AWARD at the @pencilsofpromise 15th Anniversary gala. The award is for my philanthropic achievement and impact in the world 🙏🏼😭🫶🏽 
It is truly truly such an honor to have received this award and being on the advisory board of such a beautiful charity with such a huge impact in the world alongside such giants.

I built my first school in 2022 and I can't wait to go see it when it's fully built! 🏫 
Seeing the children's faces was one of the most powerful moments I think I could have ever witnessed. Seeing the delight and hope in their eyes... the true gratitude & love in the whole community. 

Last night, I got to raise my hand at the charity gala and commit to building my 2nd school... 😍😍🏫
I share this with you to let you know the importance of giving back to the world.. this POWER we HOLD within our hearts and bank accounts..

I wake up everyday and ask myself, “Why am I here?”... I wake up everyday and re-commit to my purpose, to be a role model to my son and to someone else in the world.. to do more of what I do on a bigger scale by motivating MILLIONS of people everyday 

THAT is my purpose, and giving back is my WHY. I hope if you're reading this now, you will be a part of this journey with me and celebrate this award I received and just know if you can dream it, you can DO IT!

Someone in the world needs you too. It's up to you to connect your purpose, connect your passion to your why, connect your business to something GREATER than you.. and think everyday, “How can I possibly impact the world today?” ✍️😍
